  Msg content: '## 📅 Startup Launch Roadmap & Phases\n\n### Phase 1: MVP Setup & Foundations (Weeks 1-4)\n- **Primary Goal:** Define the core data requirements, establish the technical stack, and build the foundational data pipeline to support a basic predictive model.\n- **Key Tasks:**\n    - Finalize the specific data sources required for "Cricker Winner" predictions (historical data, stats).\n    - Select the core technology stack (Backend language, Database, Frontend framework).\n    - Design the minimum viable user flow (Input data $\\rightarrow$ Prediction Output).\n    - Set up basic cloud infrastructure (Hosting, basic database setup).\n    - Develop the initial, simplest version of the predictive algorithm (Proof-of-Concept model).\n- **Milestone:** Functional internal prototype demonstrating a prediction output based on static or manually entered data.\n\n### Phase 2: Integration & Core Features (Weeks 5-8)\n- **Primary Goal:** Build out the core prediction engine, integrate data streams, and develop the initial user interface functionality.\n- **Key Tasks:**\n    - Implement robust data ingestion pipelines from external sources.\n    - Refine and optimize the predictive model based on initial testing and data analysis.\n    - Develop the core API endpoints for serving prediction results.\n    - Design and develop the basic user interface (dashboard, input forms, result display).\n    - Implement basic user authentication (if required for saving results).\n- **Milestone:** Fully integrated system capable of generating real-time predictions and displaying them on a functional user interface.\n\n### Phase 3: Launch Prep & Alpha Testing (Weeks 9-12)\n- **Primary Goal:** Ensure system stability, execute quality assurance, establish user feedback loops, and prepare for a soft launch.\n- **Key Tasks:**\n    - Comprehensive end-to-end QA testing (data accuracy, API performance, UI responsiveness).\n    - Implement error handling and logging mechanisms.\n    - Develop user onboarding documentation and basic help guides.\n    - Execute a closed Alpha Test group to validate prediction accuracy and user experience.\n    - Finalize domain registration, basic marketing assets (screenshots, value proposition).\n    - Deploy the MVP to the live production environment.\n- **Milestone:** Successful Beta release with validated prediction accuracy and stable production infrastructure.\n\n## 💰 Budget Outline & Resource Allocation\n- **Estimated Setup Costs:**\n    - **Domain & Hosting:** \\$100 - \\$300 (Annual fees for domain and initial cloud services like AWS/GCP/Azure).\n    - **Legal/Compliance:** \\$200 - \\$500 (Basic incorporation, Terms of Service draft).\n    - **Initial Marketing/Design:** \\$500 - \\$1,500 (Simple landing page creation, initial ad testing budget).\n    - **Development Tools:** Subscription costs for necessary APIs, data services, and development licenses.\n\n- **Operational Runway Needs:**\n    - **Monthly Estimated Burn Rate:** \\$1,500 - \\$4,000 (Dependent on team size; includes cloud hosting, API fees, basic marketing spend, and salaries for core roles).\n\n- **Resource Allocation:**\n    - **Data Scientist / ML Engineer (Priority 1):** Focus on model accuracy, data cleaning, and algorithm optimization.\n    - **Full-Stack Developer (Priority 1):** Focus on API development, database integration, and frontend implementation.\n    - **Project Manager / Operations Specialist (Priority 2):** Focus on sprint planning, scope management, cross-functional communication, and ensuring lean execution.'
